.SS find
.TP
.B Summary
Search commits by optional tag and date filters.
.TP
.B Usage
.nf
omohi find [\-\-tag <tag>] [\-\-date YYYY\-MM\-DD] [\-\-output <text|json>] [\-\-field <commit_id|message|created_at>]...
.fi
.TP
.B Options
.RS 4
.B \-t, \-\-tag <tag>
optional: Filter commits by tag name.
.RE
.RS 4
.B \-d, \-\-date <YYYY\-MM\-DD>
optional: Filter commits by local date prefix.
.RE
.RS 4
.B \-\-output <text|json>
optional: Choose human\-readable text or JSON output.
.RE
.RS 4
.B \-\-field <commit_id|message|created_at>
optional, repeatable: Select one or more result fields. Repeat to keep field order.
.RE
.TP
.B Examples
.nf
omohi find
omohi find \-\-tag release
omohi find \-\-date 2026\-03\-17
omohi find \-\-tag release \-\-date 2026\-03\-17
omohi find \-\-field commit_id \-\-field created_at
omohi find \-\-output json \-\-tag release
.fi
.TP
.B Notes
.RS 4
When both filters are set, intersection is returned.
.RE
.RS 4
Each result is shown as commit ID, local timestamp, and commit message in a multi\-line block.
.RE
.RS 4
The public `created_at` field is rendered in the local timezone.
.RE
